            <div>
                <entry xml:id="L14c2dcf2180a4bc18bc30511d5965b51" n="12348">
                    <form>
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘወረደ </foreign>
                    </form>
                    <sense xml:lang="en" source="#traces" xml:id="Tmain"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                            <quote>zawarada</quote>
                        </cit> <gramGrp>
                            <pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos>
                        </gramGrp> the first week of Lent <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወበጽሑ፡ ላእካን፡ ኀበ፡ አቡነ፡ ዮናስ፡ ፬፡ ካህናት፡ ወዕለተ፡ ዐርብ፡ በቀዳሚት፡ ሰሙነ፡ አጽዋም፡</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                            <quote>The envoys, four priests, reached our father Yonas, on the Friday, in the first week of the Fasts</quote>
                        </cit>’ <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Tedros2015Yonas"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 54 (350) l. 17-18 (ed.); 55 (351) l. 18-19 (tr.) </citedRange>
                        </bibl> (‘It is the first week of the Lenten season, known as <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                            <quote>zäwärädä</quote>
                        </cit> “it descended”, which introduces the “Fast of Heraclius”. Fast is in the plural because the Lenten time comprises three events lasting fifty five days. They are: the fast of Heraclius, the forty days of our Lord's fast and finally the Week of our Lord's Passion.’ <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Tedros2015Yonas"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 55 (351) n. 72</citedRange>
                        </bibl>) <nd/> </sense>
                </entry>
